              <layoutDesc>
                <layout>Columns: 76; ruled lines: 50 51; written lines: 50 51; Uniform layout. Ruling by hard point. Visible pricking and stiching of membranes. 76 columns in total, one to six columns per membrane. No tagin on letters. In some fragments ח is arched. Special shapes of letters occur: the inverted נ placed before and after Num. 10:35-36, פ' לפוף is frequent. Columns generally begin with a new verse. Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. The "puncta extraordinaria" placed on the words fixed by masorah.</layout>
